<TITLE> 1st death anniversary of Wazed Miah observed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)  The first death anniversary of Dr Wazed Miah, nuclear scientist and husband of prime minister Sheikh Hasina, was observed at the capital on Sunday. President Zillur Rahman sent a condolence letter to the prime minister. A milad mahfil was organised at Hasina's official residence Ganabhaban after Magrib. It was attended by relatives, cabinet members, parliament members and AL leaders. Dhaka Metropolitan Awami League held a meeting and doa mahfil at their central office in memory of Wazed Miah. The programme was attended by AL leaders including deputy parliament leader Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury and state minister Sahara Khatun. Shwechha Shebak League also held a Milad at their office after Asar prayers. He died in the capital's Square Hospital on this day last year from old age complications. Wazed Miah was born on February 16, 1942 in Rangpur. His nickname was Sudha Miah. He married Sheikh Hasina on November 17, 1967. He joined the Atomic Energy Commission as a physicist in his early life and became its chairman before he retired
